    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Soak your <strong>skewers</strong> in a bowl of <strong>cold water </strong>(this prevents them from burning when cooking)</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely grate your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-cajun-style-king-prawn-skewers-w-garlic-butter-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [300ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>basmati rice & cauliflower rice</strong> to a plate and spread it out flat to help it cool down (reserve the pot!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-cajun-style-king-prawn-skewers-w-garlic-butter-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, add your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika </strong>and<strong> cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a large bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> Cajun-style seasoning</strong></p><p>Transfer <strong>half </strong>of the<strong> Cajun-style seasoning</strong> to a separate bowl and set aside (you'll use the rest later!) then drain your <strong>king prawns </strong>and combine the <strong>chopped pepper </strong>and <strong>king prawns</strong> in the large bowl of Cajun-style seasoning and then thread them onto the<strong> skewers </strong>\u2013 these are your <strong>Cajun-style king prawn skewers</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-cajun-style-king-prawn-skewers-w-garlic-butter-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>Cajun-style king prawn skewers </strong>to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 13-15 min or until the prawns are cooked through and the peppers are tender</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 trays!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-cajun-style-king-prawn-skewers-w-garlic-butter-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the skewers are cooking, chop your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped tomato</strong> and <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>to a small bowl with the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and mix to combine \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato salsa</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-cajun-style-king-prawn-skewers-w-garlic-butter-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>mayo </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the bowl of <strong>reserved Cajun-style seasoning </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and mix to combine \u2013 this is your <strong>Cajun-style sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-cajun-style-king-prawn-skewers-w-garlic-butter-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Once the butter is starting to melt, add the <strong>grated garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>cooled basmati rice</strong> and cook for 2 min or until warmed through \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic butter rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-cajun-style-king-prawn-skewers-w-garlic-butter-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>garlic butter cauliflower rice</strong> with the <strong>Cajun-style king prawn skewers </strong>and <strong>tomato salsa </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>Cajun-style sauce</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
